# Build the Time-Boxed Front Digest Section

## Question

Implement the analysis's digest contract
([Front backlog analysis](./front-backlog-analysis.svx) § "Time-boxed
Front digest contract" — the exact `FrontAggregateProjection` shape and
six render lines): the external-context digest's Front section in
joelclaw-observer consumes an aggregate projection (metadata-only
traversal like the analysis ran, bounded runtime) and renders open total
with delta, 24h/7d/30d touched windows, aged count, known-terminal
counts, and coverage — never subjects, senders, or item spillover. The
previous-snapshot comparison needs a small state file (the telemetry
watch pattern). Stale counts render as stale, never as fresh. The approved 3,000-open
ceiling is an invariant: when enumerated open exceeds it, the section
emits a HIGH gap line (feeds tick_summary and the paper health strip).
